        <p begin="00:03:17.550" end="00:03:23.610" tts:direction="ltr">But here I can see I've got this peak
<br />that's happening in the 1960s,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:23.610" end="00:03:26.450" tts:direction="ltr">16 per million births.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:26.450" end="00:03:29.450" tts:direction="ltr">Yeah. That's not very many Leans.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:29.450" end="00:03:31.990" tts:direction="ltr">Then a little bit of a dip in the 70s,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:31.990" end="00:03:35.590" tts:direction="ltr">back up in the 80s, a big dip.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:35.590" end="00:03:40.510" tts:direction="ltr">Here. Only three were named Lean in the
<br />2005.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:40.510" end="00:03:42.550" tts:direction="ltr">It's seen a little bit of popularity.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:42.550" end="00:03:47.130" tts:direction="ltr">Now, if I were to change this to the more
<br />popular spelling of Lean,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:47.130" end="00:03:49.550" tts:direction="ltr">you'll notice that this visualizer
<br />includes</p>
        <p begin="00:03:49.550" end="00:03:54.530" tts:direction="ltr">both the E ending and the A and the non
